{"title_page": "Reggie Bagala", "text_new": "{{short description|American politician}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Reggie Bagala\n| image               =\n| caption             = \n| state_house         = Louisiana\n| district            = 54th\n| term_start          = January 13, 2020\n| term_end            = April 9, 2020\n| predecessor         = [[Jerry \"Truck\" Gisclair]]\n| successor           = ''Vacant''\n| birth_name          = \n| birth_date          = 1966\n| birth_place         =\n| death_date          = {{death date and age|2020|04|09|1966|01|01}}\n| death_place         = \n| restingplace        = \n| party               = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| otherparty          = \n| father              = \n| mother              = \n| spouse              = Marissa\n| children            = 1\n| relatives           = \n| signature           = \n| alma_mater          = [[Louisiana State University]]\n}}\n\n'''Reggie Paul Bagala'''<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Live Updates: Jobless Claims Surpass 16 Million; Aid Package Stalls in Senate |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/09/us/coronavirus-us-news.html#link-66a19955 |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://justfacts.votesmart.org/candidate/biography/186985/reggie-bagala |title=Reggie Bagala's Biography |url-status=live}}</ref> (1966 \u2013 April 9, 2020) was an American politician in the state of [[Louisiana]] who served in the [[Louisiana House of Representatives]] as a member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]] in 2020.\n\n==Career==\nReggie Paul Bagala graduated from [[Louisiana State University]] in 1989.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.wdsu.com/article/louisiana-lawmaker-reggie-bagala-dies-after-battle-with-coronavirus/32100292 |title=Louisiana lawmaker Reggie Bagala dies after battle with coronavirus |date=April 9, 2020}}</ref> In 2019, he was elected to represent the 54th district in the [[Louisiana House of Representatives]].{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Death==\nOn April 1, 2020, he was tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] and got hospitalized.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.newsweek.com/louisiana-state-rep-reggie-bagala-dies-age-54-amid-battle-coronavirus-1497209 |title=LOUISIANA STATE REP. REGGIE BAGALA DIES AGE 54 AMID BATTLE WITH CORONAVIRUS |date=April 9, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410022309/https://www.newsweek.com/louisiana-state-rep-reggie-bagala-dies-age-54-amid-battle-coronavirus-1497209 |archive-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref> On April 9, Bagala died at the age of 54.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.fox8live.com/2020/04/09/louisiana-state-rep-reggie-bagala-after-battle-with-covid-coronavirus/ |title=Louisiana state Rep. Reggie Bagala dies after battle with COVID-19 coronavirus |date=April 9, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410022011/https://www.fox8live.com/2020/04/09/louisiana-state-rep-reggie-bagala-after-battle-with-covid-coronavirus/ |archive-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.reggiebagala.com/ Reggie Bagala website]\n* [https://ballotpedia.org/Reggie_Bagala at ballotpedia.org]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box | title= [[Louisiana House of Representatives|Louisiana Representatives]]<br>54th District | before= [[Jerry \"Truck\" Gisclair]]| | after=Vacant| years=2020 }}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bagala, Reggie}}\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Infectious disease deaths in Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Louisiana Republicans]]\n[[Category:Louisiana State University alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Louisiana House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:People who died in office]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American politician}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Reggie Bagala\n| image               =\n| caption             = \n| state_house         = Louisiana\n| district            = 54th\n| term_start          = January 13, 2020\n| term_end            = April 9, 2020\n| predecessor         = [[Jerry \"Truck\" Gisclair]]\n| successor           = ''Vacant''\n| birth_name          = \n| birth_date          = 1966\n| birth_place         =\n| death_date          = {{death date and age|2020|04|09|1966|01|01}}\n| death_place         = \n| restingplace        = \n| party               = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| otherparty          = \n| father              = \n| mother              = \n| spouse              = Marissa\n| children            = 1\n| relatives           = \n| signature           = \n| alma_mater          = [[Louisiana State University]]\n}}\n\n'''Reggie Paul Bagala'''<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Live Updates: Jobless Claims Surpass 16 Million; Aid Package Stalls in Senate |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/09/us/coronavirus-us-news.html#link-66a19955 |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://justfacts.votesmart.org/candidate/biography/186985/reggie-bagala |title=Reggie Bagala's Biography |url-status=live}}</ref> (1966 \u2013 April 9, 2020) was an American politician in the state of [[Louisiana]] who served in the [[Louisiana House of Representatives]] as a member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]] in 2020.\n\n==Career==\nReggie Paul Bagala graduated from [[Louisiana State University]] in 1989.<ref>{{Cite news 